EmailTemplate.subject: Evolving the Role of the Guarantor - Letter to Congress
EmailTemplate.textOnly:
Dear Colleague,
I know how committed you are to financial literacy / default prevention efforts by your partners in the student loan industry. I wanted to make sure you are aware of an initiative being undertaken by American Student Assistance (ASA) on behalf of your student loan borrowers.
I was hoping you would take a minute to look at this legislative proposal and submit a letter from you showing your support.
ASA has put forth a proposal for Title IV legislation reform that has been submitted to Congress. This proposed legislation is advocating that all borrowers as consumers are entitled to effective debt management. Universal debt management should be a right for all students; and just as students utilize deferments and forbearances, the right to debt management should be included in the law. Many other schools nationwide have expressed their support for this legislation, and I was hoping that your schoolwould be able to do so also.
I have attached a copy of the legislative proposal for your review, and if you have any questions or comments, please feel free to contact me.
If you can support this initiative, I have attached a sample letter toSenatorNelson for your convenience.
If you do send a letter, can you please send me a copy of the signed letter on school letterhead and I will forward it to our Boston office so they can cc to the relevant persons listed at the bottom of the letter. You can scan it/ e-mail it/ mail it to me; orfax it to Shaina Kalil in Boston at: 1-617-535-2554
I know the timing of this couldnt be worse, but if you would consider supporting this initiative, it would be greatly appreciated!
Thanks and good luck with all of the beginning-of-semester activity!
Steve Smith Regional Account Executive American Student Assistance 706 East Gate Drive Safety Harbor, FL 34695 800-999-9080 ext.4255 Direct:727-452-6545 ssmith@amsa.com www.amsa.com
